== Worship == Kotoshironushi is enshrined in various shrines across Japan, including {{ill|Miho Shrine|ja|美保神社}} in {{ill|Shimane Prefecture|ja|島根県}}, {{ill|Nagata Shrine|ja|長田神社}} in {{ill|Kobe|ja|神戸市}}, and {{ill|Kamo Tsuba Shrine|ja|鴨都波神社}} in {{ill|Nara Prefecture|ja|奈良県}}. The deity is also celebrated at shrines dedicated to {{ill|Ebisu|ja|えびす}}, such as {{ill|Kyoto Ebisu Shrine|ja|京都ゑびす神社}} and {{ill|Imamiya Ebisu Shrine|ja|今宮戎神社}}.
== Legends == === The Rooster Legend === In {{ill|Mihonoseki|ja|美保関町}}, a legend states that Kotoshironushi despises roosters. According to the tale, Kotoshironushi visited {{ill|Mihozuhime|ja|美保津姫}} nightly. One night, a rooster crowed prematurely, startling him, and he accidentally left his paddle behind. This led to an encounter with a crocodile (or shark), which bit his hand, causing him to resent roosters thereafter. This legend influences local customs, prohibiting the keeping of roosters or the consumption of eggs.
