In the modern period, Kotoshironushi is sometimes conflated with the deity of {{ill|Mishima Taisha|ja|三嶋大社}} in the {{ill|Izu Peninsula|ja|伊豆半島}}, where he is worshiped alongside {{ill|Ōyamazumi no Mikoto|ja|大山祇命|1=Ōyamatsumi}} as a god of island creation and fishing.

