Kotoshironushi is the principal deity of the [[Asuka Shrine|Asuka shrine]],<ref name="Ponsonby-Fane2014">{{cite book|author=R. A. B. Ponsonby-Fane|title=Studies In Shinto & Shrines|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BY23AwAAQBAJ&pg=PA499|date=3 June 2014|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-136-89294-3|pages=499–500}}</ref> and is associated with the god [[:en:Ebisu (mythology)|Ebisu]].<ref name="HavensInoue2006">{{cite book|author1=Norman Havens|author2=Nobutaka Inoue|title=An Encyclopedia of Shinto (Shinto Jiten): Kami|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=a_YQAQAAIAAJ|year=2006|publisher=Institute for Japanese Culture and Classics Kokugakuin University|isbn=978-4-905853-08-4|page=88}}</ref> In mythology, he was an adviser to [[:en:Empress Jingū|Empress Jingū]] during her invasion of [[Korea]]. He was also one of the eight deities charged with protecting the Imperial Court.<ref name="Aston2013">{{cite book|author=William Aston|title=Shinto (The Way of the Gods)|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=pOZRAgAAQBAJ&pg=PT172|date=11 December 2013|publisher=Adegi Graphics LLC|isbn=978-0-543-01408-5|page=172}}</ref> His daughter [[Himetataraisuzu-hime]] became the consort of [[:en:Emperor Jimmu|Emperor Jimmu]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Atsushi|first1=Kadoya|title=Kotoshironushi|url=http://eos.kokugakuin.ac.jp/modules/xwords/entry.php?entryID=95|publisher=Encyclopedia of Shinto|access-date=14 September 2015}}</ref>
==Overview==
{{Infobox Japanese deity | image = Nagatajinjya0906.JPG | image_size = 260px | caption = {{Center|[[Nagata Shrine]] ([[:en:Nagata-ku, Kobe|Nagata-ku, Kobe]], [[:en:Kobe|Kobe]], Hyōgo Prefecture)}} | name = Kotoshironushi no Kami | type = {{ill|Kunitsukami|ja|国津神|1=Kunitsukami|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kunitsukami|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 天津神・国津神|comment=confirming this goes to Kunitsukami|1=Kunitsukami|2=zh|3=國神|4=fr|5=Kunitsukami|6=mni|7=ꯀꯨꯅꯤꯠꯁꯨꯀꯃꯤ}} | full_name = Kotoshironushi no Kami | other_names = Yaekotoshironushi no Kami, Yaegotoshironushi no Kami, Tamakushiiribiko Iwano Kotoshiro no Kami, Tumihayahie Kotoshironushi no Kami, Shiroshi Kotoshironushi no Kami, etc. | alternative_names = {{ill|Ebisu|ja|恵比寿大神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ebisu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} | Rank = | nature = Oracle deity, Fishing deity, Crocodile deity | parents = Father: [[Ōkuninushi no Kami]]; Mother: {{ill|Kamiya Tatehime no Mikoto|ja|神屋楯比売命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamiya Tatehime no Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 神屋楯比売}} ([[:en:Kojiki|Kojiki]]) or {{ill|Takatsuhime no Kami|ja|湍津姫|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takatsuhime no Kami|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to タギツヒメ}} ([[:en:Kujiki|Sendai Kuji Hongi]]) | spouse = [[:en:Tamakushi-hime|Tamakushihime]], {{ill|Awame no Mikoto|ja|阿波咩命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Awame no Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, etc. | children = {{ill|Kushimikata no Mikoto|ja|櫛御方命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kushimikata no Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 鴨王 (上古)}}, {{ill|Hime Tatara Isuzuhime no Mikoto|ja|媛蹈鞴五十鈴媛命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hime Tatara Isuzuhime no Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to ヒメタタライスズヒメ}}, {{ill|Isuzu Yorihime no Mikoto|ja|五十鈴依姫命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Isuzu Yorihime no Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 五十鈴依媛命}}, etc. | shrines = [[:en:Miho Shrine|Miho Shrine]], {{ill|Kamo Tsuba Shrine|ja|鴨都波神社|1=Kamo Tsuba Shrine|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamo Tsuba Shrine|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamo Tsuba Shrine|qq=}}, [[:en:Nagata Shrine|Nagata Shrine]], etc. | related_clans = {{ill|Miwa clan|ja|三輪氏|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miwa clan|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 大神氏}}, {{ill|Kamo no Asomi clan|ja|賀茂氏|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamo no Asomi clan|qq=}}, {{ill|Munakata clan|ja|宗像氏|1=Munakata clan|fr|Clan Munakata|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Munakata clan|13=User:Immanuelle/Munakata clan|qq=}}, {{ill|Nagakuni no Miyatsuko|ja|長国造|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagakuni no Miyatsuko|qq=}}, {{ill|Tosa no Miyatsuko|ja|都佐国造|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tosa no Miyatsuko|qq=}}, {{ill|Hata clan|ja|波多国造|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hata clan|qq=}}, {{ill|Ishibe clan|ja|石辺氏|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ishibe clan|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} }}
'''Kotoshironushi no Kami''' ({{ill|Kotoshironushi no Kami|ja|事代主神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kotoshironushi no Kami|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 事代主}}) is a deity in [[Japanese mythology]].
== Descriptions in Historical Texts == The deity is also referred to as Yaegotoshironushi no Kami and Yaekotoshironushi no Kami. According to the [[:en:Kojiki|Kojiki]], Kotoshironushi is the child of [[Ōkuninushi]] and {{ill|Kamiya Tatehime no Mikoto|ja|神屋楯比売命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamiya Tatehime no Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 神屋楯比売}}.
During the {{ill|Ashihara no Nakatsukuni Heitei|ja|葦原中国平定|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ashihara no Nakatsukuni Heitei|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 国譲り}} (the subjugation of Ashihara no Nakatsukuni), when [[:en:Takemikazuchi|Takemikazuchi]] demanded that Ōkuninushi hand over his lands, Ōkuninushi deferred the decision to his son, Kotoshironushi. Takemikazuchi then went to {{ill|Miho no Seki|ja|美保ヶ崎|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miho no Seki|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, where Kotoshironushi agreed to relinquish the land. Following this, Kotoshironushi sank into the sea, symbolizing his retreat from worldly affairs.
== Genealogy == According to the [[:en:Kojiki|Kojiki]], Kotoshironushi is the child of [[Ōkuninushi]] and {{ill|Kamiya Tatehime no Mikoto|ja|神屋楯比売命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamiya Tatehime no Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 神屋楯比売}}. In the [[:en:Kujiki|Sendai Kuji Hongi]], the mother is listed as {{ill|Takatsuhime no Kami|ja|高津姫神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takatsuhime no Kami|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. Kotoshironushi's offspring include: - {{ill|Kushimikata no Mikoto|ja|櫛御方命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kushimikata no Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 鴨王 (上古)}} - {{ill|Hime Tatara Isuzuhime no Mikoto|ja|媛蹈鞴五十鈴媛命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hime Tatara Isuzuhime no Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to ヒメタタライスズヒメ}}, the consort of [[:en:Emperor Jimmu|Emperor Jimmu]]. - {{ill|Isuzu Yorihime no Mikoto|ja|五十鈴依姫命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Isuzu Yorihime no Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 五十鈴依媛命}}
== Worship == Kotoshironushi is enshrined in various shrines across Japan, including [[:en:Miho Shrine|Miho Shrine]] in [[:en:Shimane Prefecture|Shimane Prefecture]], [[:en:Nagata Shrine|Nagata Shrine]] in [[:en:Kobe|Kobe]], and {{ill|Kamo Tsuba Shrine|ja|鴨都波神社|1=Kamo Tsuba Shrine|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamo Tsuba Shrine|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamo Tsuba Shrine|qq=}} in [[:en:Nara Prefecture|Nara Prefecture]]. The deity is also celebrated at shrines dedicated to [[:en:Ebisu (mythology)|Ebisu]], such as {{ill|Kyoto Ebisu Shrine|ja|京都ゑびす神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kyoto Ebisu Shrine|qq=}} and [[:en:Imamiya Ebisu Shrine|Imamiya Ebisu Shrine]].
== Legends == === The Rooster Legend === In [[:en:Mihonoseki, Shimane|Mihonoseki]], a legend states that Kotoshironushi despises roosters. According to the tale, Kotoshironushi visited {{ill|Mihozuhime|ja|美保津姫|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mihozuhime|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 三穂津姫}} nightly. One night, a rooster crowed prematurely, startling him, and he accidentally left his paddle behind. This led to an encounter with a crocodile (or shark), which bit his hand, causing him to resent roosters thereafter. This legend influences local customs, prohibiting the keeping of roosters or the consumption of eggs.
=== Association with Izu === In the modern period, Kotoshironushi is sometimes conflated with the deity of [[:en:Mishima Taisha|Mishima Taisha]] in the [[:en:Izu Peninsula|Izu Peninsula]], where he is worshiped alongside {{ill|Ōyamazumi no Mikoto|ja|大山祇命|1=Ōyamatsumi|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōyamazumi no Mikoto|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōyamatsumi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to オオヤマツミ}} as a god of island creation and fishing.
